Author: BlondeActually
Text: Yes yes yes! It happens to me so often, I'm so scared of dry foods now especially.  Initially I wouldnt realize I could still breathe and I would go full on panic thinking I'm literally choking. It helps to drink something when it happens. I've gone to the ENT and everything was fine, so he referred me to a neurologist but she was rubbish and didnt even check anything.   If anyone has any clue what this is, please let me know!

Author: 25PaperCranes
Text: I get this thing where I try to spit foods that I normally wouldn’t eat out and I have to really try and suppress it around people. I think I’ve gotten that same feeling once or twice while c/sing.
